.TH "snd_ctl_sync_vmaster" 9 "snd_ctl_sync_vmaster" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ctl_sync_vmaster \- Sync the vmaster followers and hook
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_ctl_sync_vmaster
.BI "(struct snd_kcontrol *kcontrol "  ","
.BI "bool hook_only "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kcontrol" 12
vmaster kctl element
.IP "hook_only" 12
sync only the hook
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Forcibly call the put callback of each follower and call the hook function
to synchronize with the current value of the given vmaster element.
NOP when NULL is passed to \fIkcontrol\fP.
